    {
      "id": "ac72e9af-1730-4bf8-afe3-559939eb5311",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "| Algorithm | Best-case | Average-case | Worst-case | \n| --- | --- | --- | --- | \n| Timsort (Java Stream) | O(n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | \n| Merge Sort | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | \n| Quick Sort | O(n log n) | O(n log n) | O(n^2) | \n| Insertion Sort | O(n) | O(n^2) | O(n^2) |",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "ac72e9af-1730-4bf8-afe3-559939eb5311"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c9a45957-1bd3-490e-97e3-1f0fa19ac209",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Now to optimize it we can use 2 pointers. \n\nIn order to use streams to work with 2 pointers, we will first create our own [Spliterator](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Spliterator.html) by overriding [Spliterators.AbstractSpliterator](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Spliterators.AbstractSpliterator.html)",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "c9a45957-1bd3-490e-97e3-1f0fa19ac209"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "1c1f55ba-e5da-47f5-9156-c43b26436bb1",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "private static class TwoPointerSpliterator extends Spliterators.AbstractSpliterator<int[]> {\n        private int left = 0;\n        private int right;\n\n        public TwoPointerSpliterator(int[] nums) {\n            super(nums.length * (nums.length - 1) / 2, 0);\n            this.right = nums.length - 1;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean tryAdvance(java.util.function.Consumer<? super int[]> action) {\n            if (left <= right) {\n                action.accept(new int[] {left, right});\n                if (Math.abs(nums[left]) > Math.abs(nums[right])) {\n                    left++;\n                } else {\n                    right--;\n                }\n                return true;\n            }\n            return false;\n        }\n    }",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "1c1f55ba-e5da-47f5-9156-c43b26436bb1",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 70,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 70,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {},
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 70
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "68d7ad14-c581-474c-9d37-1bfa5898e51e",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "We will next use the [StreamSupport](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/StreamSupport.html) to create a stream which will stream the 2 pointers as per the 2 pointer algorithm",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "68d7ad14-c581-474c-9d37-1bfa5898e51e"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "71a007a2-dd62-4ffa-b72d-f37e5d515821",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "public static Stream<int[]> twoPointerStream(int[] nums) {\n        return StreamSupport.stream(new TwoPointerSpliterator(nums), false);\n}",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "71a007a2-dd62-4ffa-b72d-f37e5d515821",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 71,
